1
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,960
[Episode 1: Sunshine in Florida]

2
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:17,799
Black and white match.

3
00:01:17,799 --> 00:01:21,000
If you're different, step out.

4
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,079
One,

5
00:01:22,079 --> 00:01:23,480
- two, three.
<i>- If</i>

6
00:01:23,480 --> 00:01:26,719
<i>being unlikable is a talent,</i>

7
00:01:26,719 --> 00:01:29,029
<i>then I'm exceptionally gifted.</i>

8
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:32,280
<i>This is the first time I'm not it.</i>

9
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,120
<i>No one is looking for me.</i>

10
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,176
<i>They have gone home.</i>

11
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,382
Ren Xi Zhou!

12
00:01:41,879 --> 00:01:43,280
What's wrong with you?

13
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,680
So late, why aren't you home?

14
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,952
Mom, I dare not go down.

15
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,359
It's so dirty.

16
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:52,680
Alright.

17
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,180
Let's go.

18
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,920
You're fooled, you know?

19
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,920
Be smarter next time.

20
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:06,200
They said I'm your bastard.

21
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,940
That's why Dad doesn't want us.

22
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,280
If I don't pretend to fall for it,

23
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,479
they wouldn't play with a country bumpkin.

24
00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:18,400
It's not that Dad isn't coming back.

25
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,925
But that he's working outside, right?

26
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:25,360
Hong Xia, the fan is broken.

27
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,837
Coming!

28
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:43,680
Black and white match.

29
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:48,159
If you're different, step out.

30
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:51,520
- Three, two, one.
<i>- Having been it for many times,</i>

31
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,919
<i>I realized something.</i>

32
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:55,199
<i>If you sprinkle sand in clear water,</i>

33
00:02:55,199 --> 00:02:56,960
<i>everyone can see it.</i>

34
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:59,080
<i>But not murky water.</i>

35
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,159
<i>When a good kid misbehaves,</i>

36
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:03,599
<i>everyone would be disappointed in him.</i>

37
00:03:03,599 --> 00:03:05,560
<i>But a bad kid wouldn't.</i>

38
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,560
<i>A family like yours</i>

39
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,879
<i>won't have a well-educated kid.</i>

40
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:09,039
Our kid

41
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:10,800
is not for you to educate.

42
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,919
<i>I'm done talking to you.</i>

43
00:03:11,919 --> 00:03:13,680
<i>I'm going to the school to find a teacher.</i>

44
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:16,000
<i>Our kid drank the water your kid poisoned.</i>

45
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,765
<i>If anything goes wrong,
you shall be responsible.</i>

46
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,840
Nuts!

47
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:24,580
That kid's dad knows the principal.

48
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:27,760
<i>So</i>

49
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,800
<i>it's not too bad to be a bad kid.</i>

50
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,879
<i>I hear that a black-crowned night heron</i>

51
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:36,320
<i>raises its crown in danger</i>

52
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:38,599
<i>to scare off predators.</i>

53
00:03:38,599 --> 00:03:41,400
<i>Such a comical bluster</i>

54
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,759
<i>amuses everyone.</i>

55
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,919
<i>But I find it amazing.</i>

56
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:48,108
<i>Even if it's just pretending.</i>

57
00:03:48,719 --> 00:03:49,800
<i>Yes,</i>

58
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,439
<i>pretending.</i>

59
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:53,759
<i>Pretending to have a rich new dad.</i>

60
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:57,039
<i>Pretending to live a glamorous life.</i>

61
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:58,560
<i>Pretending</i>

62
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:00,311
<i>to be strong.</i>

63
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:26,600
Where did you go?

64
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,240
Zhao Qi Ming, that jerk,

65
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,439
dumped the complaining customers on us again.

66
00:04:30,439 --> 00:04:31,519
At the reception,

67
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:33,240
I just handled it.

68
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,839
Nice, Xi Zhou.

69
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:37,000
You'll definitely be promoted
to supervisor next week.

70
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,759
No doubt about it.

71
00:04:38,759 --> 00:04:41,240
I made a restaurant reservation. Join me?

72
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,091
Okay! Let's go.

73
00:04:44,199 --> 00:04:45,480
Let's toast.

74
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,639
Manager, to you.

75
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:48,042
Please.

76
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:58,519
Manager, this Merlot is for you.

77
00:04:58,519 --> 00:05:01,735
Low tannin wine is more suitable.

78
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:03,519
I have to go.

79
00:05:03,519 --> 00:05:05,560
Oh, right.
Remember to prepare your resignation.

80
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:08,029
Hand over to the new foreman
before you leave next week.

81
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:12,901
You mean... me?

82
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:16,040
We've discussed it internally.

83
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,600
Zhao Qi Ming remains as supervisor.

84
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:18,920
You're dismissed.

85
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,920
Manager He,

86
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,399
please tell me why.

87
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:23,639
- I wonder--
- You know what, Ren Xi Zhou?

88
00:05:23,639 --> 00:05:25,120
From this year on,

89
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,360
every employee receives

90
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,000
a birthday gift package.

91
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,959
A month ago,
the one sent to your address was returned.

92
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:32,960
[Crown Hotel Employee Archive]
You're not registered there.

93
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,279
You lied.

94
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:36,360
The whole staff knows.

95
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,680
They just laugh at you.

96
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,600
I don't doubt your work ability.

97
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,580
But I prefer trustworthy subordinates.

98
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:57,759
Do you know what tannin is?

99
00:05:57,759 --> 00:06:00,000
A natural phenolic compound

100
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,319
which can change the palate of wine.

101
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:04,439
Hey, Ren Xi Zhou. You're to blame.

102
00:06:04,439 --> 00:06:07,109
- When your leader corrects you--
- I paid the bill.

103
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:09,641
Any question?

104
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,340
Hi.

105
00:07:02,410 --> 00:07:04,243
["First Love" Outline Version 4]

106
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:08,282
Let me show you the sunset in Florida.

107
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,995
Gorgeous, isn't it?

108
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:34,070
Irrigate vegetables.

109
00:07:51,279 --> 00:07:52,360
The menu is on the table.

110
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:54,066
I'll be right there.

111
00:07:55,199 --> 00:07:56,752
Mom.

112
00:08:16,759 --> 00:08:18,470
A real one?

113
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,720
No.

114
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:23,320
But if you treat it as real,

115
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,716
it is.

116
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,919
That's enough, missy.

117
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,526
You don't understand.

118
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,512
Alright.

119
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:50,519
Where's Auntie Qiu?

120
00:08:50,519 --> 00:08:51,720
Grocery?

121
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:52,952
She doesn't work here anymore.

122
00:08:52,952 --> 00:08:54,280
Why?

123
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:56,808
I didn't ask you why you quit.

124
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,880
Just an annual leave.

125
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:01,531
Have you ever been home on annual leave?

126
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,720
What's the filling?

127
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,564
Too salty.

128
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:34,919
Avoid the neighbors when you go out.

129
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:36,600
So they won't keep asking.

130
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,919
They all think

131
00:09:37,919 --> 00:09:39,960
draining our savings to support your education

132
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,473
would end up with you working abroad.

133
00:09:41,473 --> 00:09:42,960
I know.

134
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:45,080
Consider finding another job.

135
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,542
I said I know.

136
00:10:35,799 --> 00:10:37,039
<i>Hello.</i>

137
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:38,440
<i>It's an adult undergraduate program.</i>

138
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,480
<i>I entered the industry early.</i>

139
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,919
<i>I worked as a forewoman</i>

140
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,520
<i>at Guangcheng Crown Hotel for three years.</i>

141
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,090
<i>I'm confident I can apply my experience</i>

142
00:10:44,090 --> 00:10:46,283
<i>to your company's work.</i>

143
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:15,760
<i>The reflection in her glasses</i>

144
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,875
<i>is so similar to Nanwan!</i>

145
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,600
<i>Could it be</i>

146
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,153
<i>that she returns?</i>

147
00:12:25,159 --> 00:12:26,679
No leftovers.

148
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:28,571
If hungry, go buy it.

149
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:37,870
You prefer strong flavors now.

150
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:42,221
You idle all day.

151
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,240
Then hire me.

152
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,844
Who cares?

153
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,240
When you're out later,

154
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:52,713
do grocery shopping.

155
00:12:53,919 --> 00:12:56,266
I'm on leave.

156
00:12:56,266 --> 00:12:58,487
We don't provide for idlers.

157
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,360
Boss, look how much I bought.

158
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,559
Give me two scallions for free.

159
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:40,840
I'm sorry, ma'am.

160
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,639
- Everyone else pays for them.
- You can have them.

161
00:13:42,639 --> 00:13:43,799
I really can't give them away.

162
00:13:43,799 --> 00:13:46,080
- Just two.
- He said no.

163
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,928
No means no.

164
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:07,517
Ren Xi Zhou?

165
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:12,112
Your hair is caught on me.

166
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,779
Take your time.

167
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,405
<i>Running into an ex in grocery shopping.</i>

168
00:14:43,534 --> 00:14:45,095
<i>Where's my grocery?</i>

169
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,492
<i>Return and get it?</i>

170
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:51,585
<i>No, no, no.</i>

171
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,919
<i>If I'm well-dressed,</i>

172
00:15:02,919 --> 00:15:04,799
<i>he'll know</i>

173
00:15:04,799 --> 00:15:06,200
<i>I lead a wonderful life</i>

174
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:08,329
<i>since we broke up.</i>

175
00:15:33,022 --> 00:15:37,009
[Hongxia Diner]
[Nanwan Liangpi]

176
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:48,062
[Hongxia Diner]
[Nanwan Liangpi]

177
00:15:52,892 --> 00:15:54,878
[Watermelon Yard]

178
00:16:10,159 --> 00:16:12,240
It's been a while.
